ntsync 1004 (combined 1004-1006): channel + thread token + RT alloc hoist

Combined patch — 1004 (channel ioctl family), 1005 (thread token
pass-through), and 1006 (slab alloc/free hoist out of raw_spinlock_t)
fold into a single chunk because they were iterated in-place against
ntsync.c.fixwork without intermediate snapshots.

1004: NTSYNC_TYPE_CHANNEL — bounded mailbox with kernel-side priority
queue and atomic priority inheritance.  Replaces Wine-NSPA's user-space
futex + manual sched_setscheduler shm-IPC fast path between client and
wineserver.

1005: thread-token pass-through for channel RECV2.  Eliminates the
userspace get_thread_from_id() lookup in the gamma dispatcher's hot
loop (~10% dispatcher CPU per 2026-04-26 perf).  Wineserver registers
(tid, token) per channel via a new ioctl; kernel returns the token
directly from RECV2.

1006: hoist all slab alloc/free out of raw_spinlock_t.  PREEMPT_RT
slab fast path uses local_lock_t which is spinlock_t (sleeping on RT),
so kzalloc()/kfree() are unsafe under raw_spinlock_t.  Six sites in
this driver violated that rule.

Regenerated 2026-05-04 from snapshot delta ntsync-p3.c → ntsync.c.post1006
(+ pristine ntsync.h → ntsync.h.post1006) to replace the original
1004/1005/1006 .patch files which had drifted from the iterated source.
Functionally identical; verified byte-identical post-1006 sources
(see project_ntsync_patches_drifted_from_fixwork.md).

